 UNDP Flag , PHOTO: devex.com  Yahya has officially commenced duties, following UN reforms that resulted in the separation of its activities from the resident coordination system. The new appointee stated yesterday in Maiduguri, “The UN General Assembly agreed to reform the UN development system by making far-reaching changes in the way the UN system works.” According to him, the reform was to help countries in their efforts to achieve the 17 Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .